---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Framework"
  description="The Poesis SAFe Agentic Framework — the open, Apache-2.0 BUILD layer that turns governed GSM definitions into runnable code."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Open · Apache-2.0</p>
      <h1>The SAFe Agentic Framework.</h1>
      <p class="lead">The open BUILD layer: SAFe-shaped multi-agent orchestration that turns governed GSM definitions into runnable code — closing THINK → BUILD → RUN.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/">Read the docs</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/poesis-cloud/safe-agentic-framework">Get it on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
      <h2>The generative bridge — and the harness that makes it trustworthy.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="card card--feature">
          <h3>Definitions that generate systems.</h3>
          <p>The framework is the BUILD layer that turns governed GSM definitions into running systems — making GSM's promise, “definitions that generate systems”, literally true, and closing THINK → BUILD → RUN as one loop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card card--feature">
          <h3>A method, run by agents, as a harness.</h3>
          <p>AI runs on intuition — exactly like we do — and methods are how intuition becomes reliable. SAFe, run by agents with a human ★ gate at every layer, is the cognitive harness that makes agentic delivery trustworthy. You don't wait for a smarter model; you make it implement a method.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-cta" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/poesis-cloud/safe-agentic-framework">Get it on GitHub</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/quickstart/">Quickstart</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
      <h2>Four functional components, one governed delivery loop.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="card"><h3>Portfolio → program → iteration</h3><p>Three orchestrators, one per SAFe layer, run an org chart of role agents — not a flat swarm — with a human ★ gate at every layer.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#orchestration">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>The specialist bench</h3><p>A bench of specialist agents — architecture, security, QA, UX and more — dispatched into each ceremony as stateless subagents.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#bench">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>The deterministic harness</h3><p>Step graphs validated by a deterministic harness — the gates, conditions, and ledger that keep probabilistic agents on rails.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#harness">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Local-first &amp; sovereign</h3><p>The agent loop runs on your machine against your working tree; work state lives in your own files and git history, not a vendor's cloud.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#local-first">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="orchestration" class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Orchestration</p>
      <h2>Portfolio → program → iteration.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Three orchestrators — one per SAFe layer — run the show from a single entry point: the portfolio layer tests the strategic bet, the program layer tests the feature shape and architecture, the iteration layer tests the code that ships. It is an org chart with human authority, not a flat swarm, with a human ★ gate at every layer.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/distributed-agentic-safe/">Distributed Agentic SAFe →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="bench" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Specialist bench</p>
      <h2>A team, not a clever individual.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Each ceremony dispatches the specialists it needs — product, architecture, security, QA, UX, DevOps — as stateless subagents that read committed artifacts and return. Division of labor makes every agent small, bounded, and accurate for its role, which is what makes a pipeline of focused agents outperform a single sprawling one.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/distributed-agentic-safe/">The agents →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="harness" class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Harness</p>
      <h2>A deterministic harness keeps agents on rails.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The workflow step graphs are validated by a deterministic harness — gates, conditions, and an append-only ledger — so the probabilistic agents move through evidence, checks, and sequence until the output is trustworthy. More governed layers across the end-to-end path produce better outcomes than a method that checks only one slice.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/">Framework overview →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="local-first" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Local-first</p>
      <h2>Local-first &amp; sovereign.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The agent loop runs on each user's machine, in the IDE, against the real working tree — your sensitive information never leaves; only the artifacts you commit sync out. Work state lives in your own files and git history (the event log), not a vendor's cloud. Nothing is trapped in an unmanaged session.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/quickstart/">Quickstart →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Build with us</p>
      <h2>Documentation &amp; source.</h2>
      <ul class="link-list">
        <li><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/">Framework documentation →</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/safe-agentic-framework/quickstart/">Quickstart →</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/poesis-cloud/safe-agentic-framework">github.com/poesis-cloud/safe-agentic-framework →</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem" class="muted">Generates from the <a href="/standard">GSM</a> standard · runs on <a href="/sie">SIE</a> · integrated into <a href="/itip">ITIP</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
